The '''BGMI Challengers Series''' is an offline tournament organized by [https://nodwingaming.com NODWIN Gaming] in collaboration with [https://www.startv.com/about-us/sports/ Star Sports], which is a qualifier for the [[BGMI Masters Series/Season 4|Masters Series Season 4]]. It features a prize pool of ₹ 6,80,000 {{Abbr/INR}} which is a part of the total ₹ 1,50,00,000 {{Abbr/INR}} prize pool

==About==
===Format===
* '''BGMI Challengers Series:''''' August 19th - September 7th, 2025
** 24 teams.
** Squads, {{Abbr/TPP}}.

* '''League Stage:''''' August 19th - 31st, 2025
** 24 teams, 13 matchdays.
** 39 matches (3 each day).
*** Each team plays a total of 26 matches.
** {{bgcolortext|up|Top 16 teams}} qualify for ''Week 3.
** {{bgcolortext|down|Bottom 8 teams}} are eliminated.
<div style="margin-top:12px"></div>
* '''League Stage Week 3:''''' September 1st - 7th, 2025
** 16 teams, 7 matchdays.
** 21 matches (3 each day).
** {{bgcolortext|up|Top 4 teams}} qualify for {{LeagueIconSmall/bgmi master series}} '''[[BGMI Masters Series/Season 4#Playoffs_2|BGMS Season 4 Playoffs]]'''
** {{bgcolortext|down|Bottom 12 teams}} are eliminated.
<br>
{{Points10|showtb=true}}

